The Nigerian Maritime Administrative & Safety Agency (NIMASA) at the weekend donated relief items  to internally displaced persons (IDP) and victims of similar disasters  in Edo State. Presenting the items to the state government on  in Benin, NIMASA Director General, Dakuku Peterside, said the donation was being carried out by the agency in 20 states of the federation affected by flood and other related disasters. Receiving the items on behalf of the state government, the senior special assistance SSA to the governor on Edo State Emergency   Management Agency (EDOSEMA), Mr Salami Luqman assured of government commitment  in ensuring judicious use of the items for the affected persons. The items includes bags of rice,  bags of beans, matrasses, blankets, sewing machines, pampers, sanitary pad and toiletries, oil, cassava and other food items worth millions of naira. Customs auctions 646 vehicles worth N272m in 6 months Customs auctions 646 vehicles worth N272m in 6 months NIMASA donates relief materials to disaster victims Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin